Package: marmap2
Type: Package
Title: Import, Plot and Analyze Bathymetric and Topographic Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person(given = "Benoît",
                    family = "Simon-Bouhet",
                    role = c("aut", "cre"),
                    email = "besibo@gmail.com"),
             person(given = "Eric",
                    family = "Pante",
                    role = "aut"))
Author: Benoît Simon-Bouhet [aut, cre], Eric Pante [aut]
Maintainer: Benoît Simon-Bouhet <besibo@gmail.com>
Depends: R (>= 2.10)
Imports: curl, ggplot2, methods, ncdf4, raster, reshape2, rlang,
        sf, tibble
Suggests: pkgdown, terra
BugReports: https://github.com/besibo/marmap2/issues
Description: Import bathymetric and hypsometric data from NOAA (National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration, <https://www.ncei.noaa.gov/products/etopo-global-relief-model>) and GEBCO (General Bathymetric Chart of the Oceans, <https://www.gebco.net>), convert historical bathy matrices to modern tabular and spatial formats, and draw bathymetric maps with ggplot2.
